     System.out.println(&quot;listFolder remotePath=&quot;+remotePath);

You are passing in &quot;remotePath=true&quot;. Fix by building the correct subPath of the sub-directory using `remotePath` as base:

      listFolder(ftp, remotePath+&quot;/&quot;+listFiles[i].getName());

Other problems are mentioned by @g00se - don&#39;t touch the ftp client inside `listFolder`, but move to the `main()`:

     ftp.connect(&quot;xxx&quot;, 21);
     ftp.enterLocalPassiveMode();
     System.out.println(&quot;successfull connected&quot;);
     ftp.login(&quot;xxx&quot;, &quot;xxx&quot;);

Finally, print stack trace in one line - or better still don&#39;t catch it and make `listFiles throws WhateverException` it leave the method so caller can decide on sensible action.

     exception.printStackTrace();

